r!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Granted catching a movie at 11am on Saturday morning is not as glamorous or romantic as a Friday night weekend kickoff, but you will find a lot more left in your pocketbook. The ticket price is usually one to two dollars less than showing movies after dark. There are some discounts at the snack counter too with coffee specials and samples of new sugary items on test with the theater.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	Aside from the monetary savings, there is less crowding in the theater allowing you and your sweetheart more room to cuddle and take your time after the movie is over to do errands or see another movie. Pretending to be a movie critic for the day! Enjoy free refills on extra-large popcorn buckets and discounted drink refills. Allow yourself the freedom to enjoy an action-flick, a romantic comedy, or a documentrary that you have been wanting to see but wasn&#39;t &quot;date material&quot;.&nbsp; A matinee movie can be a start of a great time spent together as you can catch a late lunch or head over to a community festival afterward.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The matinee or early show can save you money, time, but make a great make-up date even if you have to work late on Friday nights.</p>\r\n',NULL,NULL,'early, show, cheap, ticket, prices','Catching a film early in the day saves you money.',NULL,NULL,NULL,58,39),(234,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Film Festivals','<p>\r\n	There are several festivals throughout the year that you can plot a travel around this great United States. While film festivals can be where you find first run films and new directors, there are increasing variety of film festivals even some disguised in lore. Let&#39;s start off with the begining of the year in January, the winter locked deep would be prime time to catch a film.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In the middle of America there is Duncan, Oklahoma called the <a href=\"http://www.traildancefilmfestival.com/\">Trail Dance Film Fesitval</a> held within the Simmons Center at the recently renovated Jack. A Maurer Convention Center. There is the Golden Drover Awards Show to enjoy as this festival was listed as the one of the Movie Maker&#39;s Top 25 Coolest Film Festival in 2009.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you are looking for a bit sunnier climate the <a href=\"www.psfilmfest.org/index.aspx\">Palm Springs Internation Film Festival</a> kicks off 2011 with a complete culmation a year long festivals, parties and don&#39;t forget you can find Rodeo Drive just a few miles away in LA.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you need to grab some air and utilize that dusty umbrella, check out the <a href=\"http://www.spokanefilmfestival.org/\">SpIFF</a> or the 13th Annual Internation Film Festival to see What the World is Watching! The Spokane Internationl Film Festival keeps you on the west coast but closer to finding unique wines and one of the other Silicon Valleys.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Speaking of Silicon Valley, one of the premier film festivals featuring the Maverick award, a coveted award among independent film makers. <a href=\"http://www.cinequest.org/film_festival.php\">Cinequest </a>is the west coast rival to another film festival that is starting around the big thaw.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In Austin, Texas find yourself deep into the culture of South by Southwest or the <a href=\"http://sxsw.com\">25th SXSW</a>. This event is coveted by musicians, movie lovers, and culture alike. After catching a film, you can check out the Alamo!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Another exciting culture phenomnon in Miami, where the location is know for pushing limits, find yourself at the <a href=\"http://www.wiffonline.og\">6th Annual Women&#39;s International Film Festival </a>This event has films from everything from a pajama party to celebrities a must see especially for the air miles!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Now its, April and you have been from one coast to the other so, head north and grab the last remainig part of winter at the <a href=\"http://www.wifilfest.org\">Wisconsin Film Festival,</a> there is more than cheese there with a broad range of independent films. There is even warm hoodies to purchase for this film festival from American Apparel so be sure to pack your mittens.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Another Northern Exposure film festival will find you in Pennsylvania! The <a href=\"http://www.spririquestfilmfest.com\">Spirit Quest Film Festival </a>is held at the historic Erie Playhouse over a three day period.&nbsp; The local community is a big sponsor with Mid-Town Tattoo &amp; Piercing, Paranormal Investigations, along side the Hamilton Insurance Agency.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	While you may reserve the entire month of May for your trip to Cannes or to take your mother to France, check out a great film festival in Baltimore, Maryland home of Duff Goldman and Charm City Cakes!. The <a href=\"http://www.md-filmfest.com\">Maryland Film Festival </a>is not only affordable but you just might have some cake too while you take in some amazing films.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you are more interested in film festivals with conviction and heart you must find yourself at the <a href=\"http://www.gosprout.org/film/\">Sprout </a>Film festival in New York. This film festival aims to raise the profile of individuals with developmental disabilities by showcasing their work in all genres of our population. Sprout is the nonprofit based in NYC is the founder of this film festival that includes a Touring festival and a site featuring films specific to this festival.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Its June and that means Vegas, Baby, Vegas. The <a href=\"http://www.lvfilmfest.com\">Las Vegas Film Festival</a> offers a variety of Oscar-winning films to World Premieres complete at the Las Vegas Hilton Hotel and Casino. Remember what happens in Vegas, stays in Vegas.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If Vegas is not your style, check out Elvis&#39; home town <a href=\"http://www.memphisfilmfestival.com\">Memphis Film Festival</a> at the Whispering Woods Hotel and Convention Center in Olive Branch. This Festival is a a treat for anyone making a trip to Graceland and you can check out a ton of other music and historic place and maybe even catch a glimpse of a local who looks a lot like a <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0100405/\">Pretty Woman</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Fourth of July is approaching fast and you might find yourself in the mood for some chowder, well head on over to the <a href=\"http://www.miff.org\">13th Annual Maine International </a>Film Festival where in 10 days you get to see about 100 films but there is just more than movies at this festival many great stars have been honored here. Don&#39;t forget you can catch a jetty up to the Hamptons or Martha&#39;s Vineyard should you choose.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you don&#39;t like chowder head over to the Great Lakes in Michigan for the <a href=\"http://www.traversecityfilmfest.org\">Traverse City Film Festival </a>showing &quot;Just Great Movies&quot; This annual event is held at the historic State Theater. This festival was founded by Michael Moore so there are some amazing and enjoyable films to be found here along with Directors.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In August find yourself in North Carolina at a <a href=\"http://www.gideonfilmfestival.com\">Media Arts Conference and Film Festival.</a> The Gideon is specific to the world of Faith and featured the inspirational &quot;Letters to God&quot; flim. This film festival is part of the Film School and the Christian community.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If Gaia is more your way The event being organized by Back Roads Productions in Laytonville, CA will be the first combining Music, Community, Sustainability, and The Pursuit of Happiness. <a href=\"http://www.thegaiafestival.com\">The Gaia Festival </a>will be at Black Oak Ranch in August 2011.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Need to catch the seasons change and maybe find an accent, there is the 27th Annual <a href=\"http://www.bostonfilmfestival.org\">Boston Film Festival</a> will help especially if you can catch stars like George Clooney or Sam Mendes. The BFF is a top pick to go and do on every list.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	School starts in September and maybe to find yourself in the District of Columbia watching a short film. This film festival is focused solely on the true independent short films. Catch a glimpse of the President or walk on K Street before you catch a great film or two. The <a href=\"http://www.dcshorts.com\">DC Shorts Film Festiva</a>l tagline is Keep it Short Keep it Reel and you should too!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	As Fall begins, head over to the magestic Jackson Hole Wyoming and stay at the Jackson Lake Lodge while you enjoy the <a href=\"http://www.jhfestival.org\">Jackson Hole Wildlife Film</a> Festival. This biennial festival is a collaboration of over 650 professionals that will highlight the last 20 years of natural history filmmaking and what the next 20 years holds.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Catch Halloween in the South at the <a href=\"http://filmfest.scad.edu/\">Savannah Film Festiva</a>l this online submission based film festival also features grants and can find yourself on a plantation not to unlike Gone with the Wind. Its Peachy!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Feeling like the ghouls of the holidays are fast approaching, well there is something more scary than the relatives coming over for the Holidays. <a href=\"http://www.crypticonminneapolis.com/\">Cyrpticon Minneapolis </a>is one stop for not only to see the Worlds Largest Mall and some football but, to get a good fright before you go out in the night!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Keeping in the cinematic theme and you head over to Indiana, you might find yourself a <a href=\"http://www.darkcarnivalfilmfest.com/\">Dark Carnival</a>. This film festival held in Bloomington Indiana at the Indiana University where the average temperature is 35 degrees perfect for a gory thrill.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Okay, Santa Claus is on his way and you can find yourself in your local theater celebrating great classic holiday films like The Christmas Story and White Christmas or the Nightmare Before Christmas. So if you haven&#39;t found at least one good Film Festival to attend then look up Comic-Con series of events or even a few Art &amp; Wine events that feature some nuggets.</p>\r\n',NULL,NULL,'first, run, movies, independent, festival, community','Film Festivals are great way to find gem movies.',NULL,NULL,NULL,58,36),(235,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Become a guinea pig ','<p>\r\n	Want to catch a free movie or find out about the summer blockbuster before anyone else. You don&#39;t want to shell out hard earned cash check out three ways to save you a dime or two. The first is the most work and not always fruitful but, sign up and enter to win tickets with local television, radio and theaters. Unfortunately, this puts your information on a mailing contact list, so be sure to mark the information Private so that you don&#39;t get added to a mass mailing list. The second opportunity is to ask the cinema manager as they are notified by local marketers and distributors. It is not as simply as asking the manager, you usually have to join the theater group and work your way into the good graces. The third is to join a group on a social site that has sponsors from theaters.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	There are sites like FilmMetro.com and such that may get you to one film you want to see once in while but for the easy sign up you may receive hundreds of emails but, try it anyway.</p>\r\n',NULL,NULL,'test, audience, movie, ','Find out how to earn extra perk at the movie theater by being a guinea pig.',NULL,NULL,NULL,58,36),(236,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Internet Marketing','<p>\r\n	A sound marketing startegy works for the promotion of any product. {{The moment you {{plan | decide | contemplate}} to sell your product through internet then it is vital to plan your marekting strategy. | If you intend to sell you product through internet then you must also plan an internet marketing strategy.}} {{Its highly important that your site gets noticed by the search engines. | Its very important for you to build your web presence.| Its important that peoplpe find your web site when they